BNP Paribas, EDF and Thales: French Equity Preview

-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 
2011-09-19T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/bnp-paribas-edf-and-thales-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  France ’s benchmark CAC 40 Index fell 0.5 percent to
3,031.08 while the broader SBF 120 Index declined 0.4 percent to
2,326.02.  BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA: BNP Paribas Fortis, the Belgian
retail-banking unit of France’s largest lender, plans a cost-
cutting program to save about 200 million euros ($276 million) a
year, De Tijd reported. The shares fell 7.6 percent to 28.20
euros.  Electricite de France SA (EDF FP): Edison SpA’s Italian
investors may give their stake in Electricite de France in
exchange for 50 percent of the Milan-based utility’s Edipower
unit, Il Sole 24 Ore reported, without saying where it got the
information. EDF’s shares rose 2.9 percent to 21.22 euros.  Thales SA (HO)  : The French defense electronics company
hired  Barclays Capital  to help to sell a unit, which trains
Boeing 787 and Airbus A380 pilots, the Sunday Times reported,
without saying where it got the information. The business, which
offers flight simulation services, may be worth about 200
million pounds ($316 million), the newspaper said. The shares
rose 1.1 percent to 26.29 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabio Benedetti-Valentini in Paris at 
 fabiobv@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net . 